com.isbx.locationtools

Class DirectionsRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.isbx.locationtools.DirectionsRequest

  • public class DirectionsRequest
extends Object
    A helper class for making requests to Google's Directions API.

    By default, this will make anonymous requests directly to the Directions API endpoint, which is subject to stricter rate limiting quotas. If you wish to use an API key instead, the recommended approach is to obtain a server key and set up your own remote server to proxy requests from the mobile client to the Directions API. To support this, you can optionally specify a custom endpoint url pointing to your remote server. Your custom endpoint will be expected to conform to the same specification as the Directions API for the origin and destination parameters.
